---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';
import SidePanel from '../../../components/SidePanel.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Storehaus RTS Privacy Policy | Team Respawn"
  description="Privacy Policy for the Storehaus RTS Discord Bot. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your information."
  keywords="Storehaus RTS, privacy policy, Discord bot, data protection"
  canonical="https://www.teamrespawn.net/storehaus/privacy-policy"
  ogTitle="Storehaus RTS Privacy Policy | Team Respawn"
  ogDescription="Privacy Policy for the Storehaus RTS Discord Bot. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your information."
  ogImage="https://www.teamrespawn.net/content/Team-Respawn-Full.png"
>
  <a
    href="#main-content"
    class="sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:absolute focus:top-4 focus:left-4 focus:z-50 focus:bg-white focus:text-black focus:px-4 focus:py-2 focus:rounded"
  >
    Skip to main content
  </a>

  <div class="container mx-auto p-4 sm:p-8">
    <Header />

    <main id="main-content" class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-8" role="main" aria-label="Privacy Policy content">
      <article class="bg-gray-800/60 border border-gray-700/60 rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-8 lg:p-10">
        <header class="mb-8">
          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-extrabold mb-4 text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-400 to-pink-400">
            Privacy Policy
          </h1>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg">
            <strong>Last Updated:</strong> January 2026
          </p>
        </header>

        <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-300">Introduction</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              This Privacy Policy describes how the Storehaus RTS Discord Bot ("the Bot", "we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, and protects information when you interact with it on Discord. We are committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about our data practices.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-300">Information We Collect</h2>

            <h3 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-purple-200 mt-6">Discord Data</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              When you use the Bot, Discord automatically provides certain information through their API, including:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
              <li><strong>User ID</strong>: Your unique Discord user identifier</li>
              <li><strong>Username and Display Name</strong>: Your Discord username and server display name</li>
              <li><strong>Guild/Server ID</strong>: The unique identifier of the Discord server where you use the Bot</li>
              <li><strong>Channel ID</strong>: The unique identifier of the channel where commands are used</li>
              <li><strong>Message Content</strong>: The content of slash commands and interactions you send to the Bot</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              <strong>Important:</strong> While Discord provides this information to the Bot, <strong>we do not store or log Discord user IDs, guild IDs, usernames, or any personally identifiable information (PII)</strong> in our databases.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-purple-200 mt-6">Command Usage Data</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              When you use Bot commands, we may temporarily process:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
              <li><strong>Command Input</strong>: The parameters you provide to commands (e.g., search queries, player IDs, questions)</li>
              <li><strong>Command Type</strong>: Which command was executed</li>
              <li><strong>Timestamp</strong>: When the command was executed</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-purple-200 mt-6">Query Logs (Halo Wars 2 AI Feature)</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              For the <code class="bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded text-purple-300">/hw2ask</code> command, we log queries to improve the service quality. <strong>These logs do NOT include any user-identifying information.</strong> We only store:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
              <li>The question text</li>
              <li>Query type and confidence level</li>
              <li>Response metadata (model used, response time, sources referenced)</li>
              <li>Timestamp</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              <strong>We explicitly do NOT store:</strong>
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
              <li>Your Discord user ID</li>
              <li>Your username</li>
              <li>Server or channel information</li>
              <li>Any other personally identifiable information</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-300">How We Use Information</h2>

            <h3 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-purple-200 mt-6">Service Provision</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We use the information provided by Discord to:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
              <li>Process and respond to your commands</li>
              <li>Provide game statistics and information</li>
              <li>Answer strategy questions through our AI-powered features</li>
              <li>Ensure proper command functionality</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-purple-200 mt-6">Analytics and Improvement</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We use anonymized query logs to:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
              <li>Improve response quality and accuracy</li>
              <li>Understand common questions and topics</li>
              <li>Monitor service performance</li>
              <li>Identify areas for improvement</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              All analytics are performed on anonymized data without any user identifiers.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-300">Data Storage</h2>

            <h3 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-purple-200 mt-6">What We Store</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
              <li><strong>Query Logs</strong>: Anonymized questions and response metadata (no user IDs)</li>
              <li><strong>Game Data</strong>: Public game information (units, civilizations, statistics)</li>
              <li><strong>Vector Embeddings</strong>: Processed game data for AI search functionality</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-purple-200 mt-6">What We Do NOT Store</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
              <li>Discord user IDs</li>
              <li>Discord usernames or display names</li>
              <li>Guild/Server IDs</li>
              <li>Channel IDs</li>
              <li>Message content (except anonymized questions for <code class="bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded text-purple-300">/hw2ask</code>)</li>
              <li>Any personally identifiable information</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-purple-200 mt-6">Storage Location</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
              <li>Query logs are stored locally in SQLite databases</li>
              <li>Game data is stored locally in JSON files</li>
              <li>Vector embeddings are stored locally in ChromaDB</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              All data is stored on the Bot operator's infrastructure and is not shared with third parties except as described below.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-300">Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              The Bot uses the following third-party services:
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-purple-200 mt-6">Discord</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
              <li><strong>Purpose</strong>: Bot platform and command processing</li>
              <li><strong>Data Shared</strong>: Command interactions (handled by Discord's infrastructure)</li>
              <li><strong>Privacy Policy</strong>: <a href="https://discord.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-purple-400 hover:text-purple-300 underline">Discord Privacy Policy</a></li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-purple-200 mt-6">aoe4world.com API</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
              <li><strong>Purpose</strong>: Fetching Age of Empires IV statistics and player data</li>
              <li><strong>Data Shared</strong>: Public player IDs and game statistics (publicly available data)</li>
              <li><strong>Privacy Policy</strong>: <a href="https://aoe4world.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-purple-400 hover:text-purple-300 underline">aoe4world.com Terms</a></li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-purple-200 mt-6">LLM Providers (Groq, Cloudflare, OpenRouter, Cerebras)</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
              <li><strong>Purpose</strong>: Generating AI-powered responses for strategy questions</li>
              <li><strong>Data Shared</strong>: Anonymized questions (no user identifiers)</li>
              <li>
                <strong>Privacy Policies</strong>:
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
                  <li><a href="https://groq.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-purple-400 hover:text-purple-300 underline">Groq Privacy Policy</a></li>
                  <li><a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-purple-400 hover:text-purple-300 underline">Cloudflare Privacy Policy</a></li>
                  <li><a href="https://openrouter.ai/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-purple-400 hover:text-purple-300 underline">OpenRouter Privacy Policy</a></li>
                  <li><a href="https://www.cerebras.net/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-purple-400 hover:text-purple-300 underline">Cerebras Privacy Policy</a></li>
                </ul>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-300">Data Retention</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
              <li><strong>Query Logs</strong>: Retained indefinitely for analytics and service improvement</li>
              <li><strong>Discord Data</strong>: Not stored; only processed temporarily during command execution</li>
              <li><strong>Game Data</strong>: Retained as long as the Bot is operational</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-300">Your Rights</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Since we do not store personally identifiable information, traditional data subject rights (such as data deletion requests) do not apply in the same way. However:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
              <li><strong>Anonymized Query Logs</strong>: If you have concerns about specific queries, you can contact the Bot operator</li>
              <li><strong>No User Tracking</strong>: We cannot track or identify individual users as we don't store user identifiers</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-300">Security</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We implement reasonable security measures to protect the data we store:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
              <li>Local storage of databases and files</li>
              <li>No transmission of user identifiers to external services</li>
              <li>Anonymized logging practices</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              However, no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure. While we strive to protect your privacy, we cannot guarantee absolute security.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-300">Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              The Bot is not intended for users under the age of 13. Discord's Terms of Service require users to be at least 13 years old. We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-300">Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The "Last Updated" date at the top indicates when changes were made. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-300">Contact</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact the Bot operator through the Discord server where the Bot is hosted.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-300">Compliance</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              This Privacy Policy is designed to comply with:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 space-y-2 text-gray-300 ml-4">
              <li>Discord's Developer Terms of Service</li>
              <li>General data protection principles</li>
              <li>Best practices for privacy-first bot development</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <footer class="mt-8 pt-6 border-t border-gray-700">
            <p class="text-gray-400 italic">
              <strong>Note:</strong> This Bot is operated independently and is not affiliated with Microsoft, 343 Industries, Relic Entertainment, or any game publishers. All game data and statistics are provided for informational purposes only.
            </p>
          </footer>
        </div>
      </article>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </div>

  <SidePanel />

  <script src="/js/side-panel.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/tabs.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/dropdowns.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/secondary-init.js" is:inline></script>
</BaseLayout>
